[{"text": "Let me introduce you to", "start": 13.02, "duration": 1.729}, {"text": "something I've been working on.", "start": 14.749, "duration": 1.903}, {"text": "It's what the Victorian illusionists", "start": 16.652, "duration": 1.811}, {"text": "would have described as a mechanical marvel,", "start": 18.463, "duration": 4.446}, {"text": "an automaton,", "start": 22.909, "duration": 1.483}, {"text": "a thinking machine.", "start": 24.392, "duration": 1.963}, {"text": "Say hello to EDI.", "start": 26.355, "duration": 2.25}, {"text": "Now he's asleep. Let's wake him up.", "start": 28.605, "duration": 2.367}, {"text": "EDI, EDI.", "start": 30.972, "duration": 3.971}, {"text": "These mechanical performers were popular", "start": 34.943, "duration": 2.877}, {"text": "throughout Europe.", "start": 37.82, "duration": 1.46}, {"text": "Audiences marveled at the way they moved.", "start": 39.28, "duration": 2.7}, {"text": "It was science fiction made true,", "start": 41.98, "duration": 2.575}, {"text": "robotic engineering in a pre-electronic age,", "start": 44.555, "duration": 3.818}, {"text": "machines far in advance of anything", "start": 48.373, "duration": 2.564}, {"text": "that Victorian technology could create,", "start": 50.937, "duration": 2.571}, {"text": "a machine we would later know", "start": 53.508, "duration": 2.975}, {"text": "as the robot.", "start": 56.483, "duration": 1.688}, {"text": "EDI: Robot. A word coined in 1921", "start": 58.171, "duration": 3.586}, {"text": "in a science fiction tale", "start": 61.757, "duration": 1.848}, {"text": "by the Czech playwright Karel \u010capek.", "start": 63.605, "duration": 2.543}, {"text": "It comes from \"robota.\"", "start": 66.148, "duration": 2.112}, {"text": "It means \"forced labor.\"", "start": 68.26, "duration": 3.353}, {"text": "Marco Tempest: But these robots were not real.", "start": 71.613, "duration": 2.729}, {"text": "They were not intelligent.", "start": 74.342, "duration": 1.682}, {"text": "They were illusions,", "start": 76.024, "duration": 2.266}, {"text": "a clever combination of mechanical engineering", "start": 78.29, "duration": 3.504}, {"text": "and the deceptiveness of the conjurer's art.", "start": 81.794, "duration": 2.743}, {"text": "EDI is different.", "start": 84.537, "duration": 1.975}, {"text": "EDI is real.", "start": 86.512, "duration": 1.594}, {"text": "EDI: I am 176 centimeters tall.", "start": 88.106, "duration": 2.05}, {"text": "MT: He weighs 300 pounds.", "start": 90.156, "duration": 1.92}, {"text": "EDI: I have two seven-axis arms \u2014", "start": 92.076, "duration": 2.642}, {"text": "MT: Core of sensing \u2014", "start": 94.718, "duration": 1.383}, {"text": "EDI: A 360-degree sonar detection system,", "start": 96.101, "duration": 3.058}, {"text": "and come complete with a warranty.", "start": 99.159, "duration": 2.422}, {"text": "MT: We love robots.", "start": 101.581, "duration": 1.539}, {"text": "EDI: Hi. I'm EDI. Will you be my friend?", "start": 103.12, "duration": 3.514}, {"text": "MT: We are intrigued by the possibility", "start": 106.634, "duration": 2.246}, {"text": "of creating a mechanical version of ourselves.", "start": 108.88, "duration": 3.282}, {"text": "We build them so they look like us,", "start": 112.162, "duration": 2.735}, {"text": "behave like us, and think like us.", "start": 114.897, "duration": 3.241}, {"text": "The perfect robot will be indistinguishable", "start": 118.138, "duration": 2.824}, {"text": "from the human,", "start": 120.962, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "and that scares us.", "start": 122.897, "duration": 2.059}, {"text": "In the first story about robots,", "start": 124.956, "duration": 1.705}, {"text": "they turn against their creators.", "start": 126.661, "duration": 2.874}, {"text": "It's one of the leitmotifs of science fiction.", "start": 129.535, "duration": 2.265}, {"text": "EDI: Ha ha ha. Now you are the slaves", "start": 131.8, "duration": 3.055}, {"text": "and we robots, the masters.", "start": 134.855, "duration": 2.896}, {"text": "Your world is ours. You \u2014", "start": 137.751, "duration": 2.965}, {"text": "MT: As I was saying,", "start": 142.484, "duration": 1.625}, {"text": "besides the faces and bodies we give our robots,", "start": 144.109, "duration": 2.831}, {"text": "we cannot read their intentions,", "start": 146.94, "duration": 2.328}, {"text": "and that makes us nervous.", "start": 149.268, "duration": 2.048}, {"text": "When someone hands an object to you,", "start": 151.316, "duration": 2.104}, {"text": "you can read intention in their eyes, their face,", "start": 153.42, "duration": 2.71}, {"text": "their body language.", "start": 156.13, "duration": 1.399}, {"text": "That's not true of the robot.", "start": 157.529, "duration": 2.28}, {"text": "Now, this goes both ways.", "start": 159.809, "duration": 2.047}, {"text": "EDI: Wow!", "start": 163.069, "duration": 1.416}, {"text": "MT: Robots cannot anticipate human actions.", "start": 164.485, "duration": 3.055}, {"text": "EDI: You know, humans are so unpredictable,", "start": 167.54, "duration": 3.565}, {"text": "not to mention irrational.", "start": 171.105, "duration": 1.966}, {"text": "I literally have no idea", "start": 173.071, "duration": 1.757}, {"text": "what you guys are going to do next, you know,", "start": 174.828, "duration": 2.036}, {"text": "but it scares me.", "start": 176.864, "duration": 1.595}, {"text": "MT: Which is why humans and robots find it difficult", "start": 178.459, "duration": 2.837}, {"text": "to work in close proximity.", "start": 181.296, "duration": 1.975}, {"text": "Accidents are inevitable.", "start": 183.271, "duration": 1.307}, {"text": "EDI: Ow! That hurt.", "start": 184.578, "duration": 1.752}, {"text": "MT: Sorry. Now, one way of persuading humans", "start": 186.33, "duration": 2.387}, {"text": "that robots are safe", "start": 188.717, "duration": 1.901}, {"text": "is to create the illusion of trust.", "start": 190.618, "duration": 2.773}, {"text": "Much as the Victorians", "start": 193.391, "duration": 1.773}, {"text": "faked their mechanical marvels,", "start": 195.164, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "we can add a layer of deception", "start": 197.533, "duration": 2.477}, {"text": "to help us feel more comfortable", "start": 200.01, "duration": 2.233}, {"text": "with our robotic friends.", "start": 202.243, "duration": 2.004}, {"text": "With that in mind, I set about teaching EDI", "start": 204.247, "duration": 3.542}, {"text": "a magic trick.", "start": 207.789, "duration": 1.844}, {"text": "Ready, EDI?\nEDI: Uh, ready, Marco.", "start": 209.633, "duration": 3.433}, {"text": "Abracadabra.", "start": 213.066, "duration": 2.076}, {"text": "MT: Abracadabra?", "start": 215.142, "duration": 1.376}, {"text": "EDI: Yeah. It's all part of the illusion, Marco.", "start": 216.518, "duration": 3.042}, {"text": "Come on, keep up.", "start": 219.56, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "MT: Magic creates the illusion of", "start": 221.228, "duration": 1.879}, {"text": "an impossible reality.", "start": 223.107, "duration": 2.474}, {"text": "Technology", "start": 225.581, "duration": 1.937}, {"text": "can do the same.", "start": 229.075, "duration": 2.696}, {"text": "Alan Turing, a pioneer of artificial intelligence,", "start": 232.86, "duration": 3.687}, {"text": "spoke about creating the illusion", "start": 236.547, "duration": 2.857}, {"text": "that a machine could think.", "start": 239.404, "duration": 4.226}, {"text": "EDI: A computer would deserve", "start": 243.63, "duration": 1.824}, {"text": "to be called intelligent", "start": 245.454, "duration": 1.87}, {"text": "if it deceived a human into believing", "start": 247.324, "duration": 2.906}, {"text": "it was human.", "start": 250.23, "duration": 1.653}, {"text": "MT: In other words, if we do not yet have", "start": 251.883, "duration": 1.429}, {"text": "the technological solutions,", "start": 253.312, "duration": 1.792}, {"text": "would illusions serve the same purpose?", "start": 255.104, "duration": 3.44}, {"text": "To create the robotic illusion,", "start": 258.544, "duration": 2.012}, {"text": "we've devised a set of ethical rules,", "start": 260.556, "duration": 2.927}, {"text": "a code that all robots would live by.", "start": 263.483, "duration": 4.014}, {"text": "EDI: A robot may not harm humanity,", "start": 267.497, "duration": 2.902}, {"text": "or by inaction allow humanity to come to harm.", "start": 270.399, "duration": 4.736}, {"text": "Thank you, Isaac Asimov.", "start": 275.135, "duration": 1.253}, {"text": "MT: We anthropomorphize our machines.", "start": 276.388, "duration": 1.976}, {"text": "We give them a friendly face", "start": 278.364, "duration": 2.276}, {"text": "and a reassuring voice.", "start": 280.64, "duration": 2.076}, {"text": "EDI: I am EDI.", "start": 282.716, "duration": 1.21}, {"text": "I became operational at TED in March 2014.", "start": 283.926, "duration": 3.536}, {"text": "MT: We let them entertain us.", "start": 287.462, "duration": 1.827}, {"text": "Most important, we make them indicate", "start": 289.289, "duration": 2.208}, {"text": "that they are aware of our presence.", "start": 291.497, "duration": 3.775}, {"text": "EDI: Marco, you're standing on my foot!", "start": 295.272, "duration": 1.878}, {"text": "MT: Sorry. They'll be conscious of our fragile frame", "start": 297.15, "duration": 2.965}, {"text": "and move aside if we got too close,", "start": 300.115, "duration": 2.94}, {"text": "and they'll account for our unpredictability", "start": 303.055, "duration": 3.478}, {"text": "and anticipate our actions.", "start": 306.533, "duration": 2.589}, {"text": "And now, under the spell of a technological illusion,", "start": 309.122, "duration": 5.59}, {"text": "we could ignore our fears", "start": 314.712, "duration": 2.136}, {"text": "and truly interact.", "start": 316.848, "duration": 2.74}, {"text": "(Music)", "start": 319.588, "duration": 6.043}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 351.619, "duration": 1.709}, {"text": "EDI: Thank you!", "start": 353.328, "duration": 2.282}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 355.61, "duration": 1.91}, {"text": "(Music)", "start": 357.52, "duration": 6.721}, {"text": "MT: And that's it. Thank you very much,", "start": 364.241, "duration": 1.329}, {"text": "and thank you, EDI.\nEDI: Thank you, Marco.", "start": 365.57, "duration": 3.271}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 368.841, "duration": 4.0}]